The U.S. government often enforces sanctions by weaponizing the dollar, which not only hurts the economies targeted, but also other economies and their peoples as well. As a result, U.S. weaponization of its currency dominance will eventually force others to develop their own payment mechanisms that will undermine the dollar's primacy in the long run. Credits: Editor: Yuan Xin Designer: Cao Yi Senior producer: Wei Wei Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)